#include <iostream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::string str;
    std::cout << "Enter a string: ";
    std::cin >> str;
    int len = str.length();
    for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
        std::cout << str[len - i - 1];
    }
    return 0;
}
```

This code will prompt the user to enter a string, store the input in the `str` variable, and then print the characters of the string in reverse order. The loop iterates `len` times, where `len` is the length of the string, and prints each character at index `len - i - 1`, effectively reversing the string.
